"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58301","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-12","<p>DECC Ministers and officials meet energy company representatives on a regular basis to discuss market issues.</p><p>It is important that all consumers, including carers, have access to information to help them make informed decisions about their energy use. That is why Ofgem introduced a new simpler tariff framework consisting of a tariff information label and tariff comparison rate to make it easier for consumers to compare tariffs across the market. In April Ofgem launched the ‘Be An Energy Shopper' campaign to empower consumers to shop around for a better deal for their energy.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","199156","2014-06-12T14:05:21.290243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58301/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58301/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-05","Energy: Carers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of provision of information for carers on affordable energy.","false","Biography information for John Robertson","Glasgow North West","John Robertson","199155"
