"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58310","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-12","<p /> <p /> <p>Current resourcing data shows the full time equivalent staff employed to work exclusively on Universal Credit. In total this is (a) 535.8 comprising of (b) 21 in Communications (c) 80.8 in IT Development and (d) 434 in Project Delivery.</p><p> </p><p>These figures exclude contractors.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-12T16:16:28.6687393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58310/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58310/answer","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58310/answer/previousversion/524","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58310/answer/previousversion/524",,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-05","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many full-time equivalent staff are employed by his Department to work exclusively on universal credit in (a) total, (b) communications, (c) IT development and (d) project delivery.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","199314"
