"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58313","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-12","<p>UK direct financial assistance to the Palestinian Authority is channelled through the World Bank Palestinian Reform and Development Plan Trust Fund and is used to pay the salaries of civil servants from an approved list. The list of individuals is systematically screened and checked against international (including Israeli) and ad hoc sanctions lists. The whole process is independently audited which ensures we know exactly where and how our money is being spent.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-06-12T14:02:27.8084035Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58313/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58313/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-05","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what arrangements are in place to monitor the use of funds given to the Palestinian Authority.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","199229"
