"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57644","Home Office","false","2014-06-10","<p> </p><p>The following table contains the requested data and covers the period up until <br>30 September 2013. Figures as at 31 March 2014 are due to be published 17 July <br>2014.</p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green","198505","2014-06-10T13:01:00.5220778Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57644/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57644/answer","PQ198505-198506  table.xlsx","PQ198505-198506  table.xlsx","Full-time equivalent officers","Full-time equivalent officers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57644/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-04","North Yorkshire Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many full-time equivalent (a) police officers, (b) police community support officers and (c) police civilian staff were employed by North Yorkshire police on (i) 31 March and (ii) 30 September in each year since 2004.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","198506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57645","Home Office","false","2014-06-10","<p> </p><p>The information requested is shown in the following table.<br><br>Most of this information was also published by the Home Office in its &quot;Crimes <br>Detected in England and Wales, 2012/13&quot; bulletin. Overall detection rates are <br>available in table 3 for all police forces from the year 2005/06 onwards.<br><br>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/224022<br>/hosb0213-pfatabs.ods <br><br>Detections have now been replaced by a new outcomes framework, which includes a <br>broader range of &quot;outcomes&quot; for crimes dealt with by the police, and therefore <br>provides greater transparency on how crimes are resolved. The former detections <br>framework only covered a subset of the new outcomes and therefore of the ways <br>crimes are &quot;resolved&quot;. Statistics for the year 2013/14 onwards will focus on <br>the new outcomes framework, rather than detections.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-06-10T12:46:04.1913784Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57645/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57645/answer","PQ198507 - table.xls","PQ198507 - table.xls","Crime detection rate for North Yorkshire Police","Crime detection rate for North Yorkshire Police","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57645/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-04","North Yorkshire Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the crime detection rate was for North Yorkshire police force in each year since 2004-05.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","198507"
